definition.value: A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the  conjugate base of allantoic acid.
A dipeptide composed of L-tyrosine and L-arginine joined by a peptide linkage.
An octadeca-9,11-dienoate that is the conjugate base of 9-cis,11-trans-octadecadienoic acid, formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid functional group.
A beta-D-galactopyranoside having a methyl substituent at the anomeric position.
